18/05/2005
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegro's Parliament debated the opposition's request for a no-confidence motion against the cabinet of Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic on Tuesday (17 May). The opposition parties blame the government for the country's weak economy and for failing to combat corruption and organised crime. The debate was to continue Wednesday. (Mina, Tanjug, B92 - 17/05/05)
